1
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:11,682
Sometimes, I think I'm cursed.

2
00:01:12,143 --> 00:01:14,746
Because of something that happened before I was even born.

3
00:01:15,742 --> 00:01:17,607
See, a long time ago,

4
00:01:17,609 --> 00:01:18,829
there was this family.

5
00:01:20,122 --> 00:01:22,076
The Papá, he was a musician.

6
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:25,586
He and his family would sing and dance

7
00:01:25,588 --> 00:01:26,909
and count their blessings.

8
00:01:27,963 --> 00:01:29,554
But he also had a dream.

9
00:01:29,840 --> 00:01:31,807
To play for the world.

10
00:01:34,678 --> 00:01:35,622
And one day,

11
00:01:36,892 --> 00:01:38,538
he left with his guitar,

12
00:01:39,611 --> 00:01:40,925
and never returned.

13
00:01:49,318 --> 00:01:50,271
And the Mamá.

14
00:01:51,028 --> 00:01:53,734
She didn't have time to cry over that walk-away musician.

15
00:01:56,199 --> 00:01:58,979
After banishing all music from her life

16
00:02:00,370 --> 00:02:02,543
she found a way to provide for her daughter.

17
00:02:06,668 --> 00:02:08,131
She rolled up her sleeves,

18
00:02:08,410 --> 00:02:10,166
and she learned to make shoes.

19
00:02:15,218 --> 00:02:17,197
She could have made candy,

20
00:02:18,126 --> 00:02:19,191
or fireworks,

21
00:02:19,586 --> 00:02:21,727
or sparkly underwear for wrestlers,

22
00:02:22,683 --> 00:02:23,885
but no,

23
00:02:24,346 --> 00:02:25,992
she chose shoes.

24
00:02:28,523 --> 00:02:30,571
Then she taught her daughter to make shoes.

25
00:02:32,152 --> 00:02:33,193
And later,

26
00:02:33,195 --> 00:02:34,704
she taught her son-in-law.

27
00:02:35,864 --> 00:02:37,833
Then her grandkids got roped in.

28
00:02:39,409 --> 00:02:40,727
As her family grew,

29
00:02:40,935 --> 00:02:42,385
so did the business.

30
00:02:43,872 --> 00:02:46,421
Music had torn her family apart.

31
00:02:47,501 --> 00:02:49,549
But shoes held them all together.

32
00:02:51,421 --> 00:02:52,657
You see that woman,

33
00:02:53,097 --> 00:02:54,529
was my great great-grandmother,

34
00:02:54,531 --> 00:02:55,609
Mamá Imelda.

35
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:59,143
She died way before I was born.

36
00:02:59,596 --> 00:03:01,849
But my family still tells her story

37
00:03:01,851 --> 00:03:04,305
every year on Día de los Muertos.

38
00:03:04,382 --> 00:03:05,725
The Day of the Dead.

39
00:03:06,174 --> 00:03:07,505
And her little girl,

40
00:03:07,780 --> 00:03:09,159
she's my great-grandmother,

41
00:03:09,161 --> 00:03:10,008
Mamá Coco.

42
00:03:10,941 --> 00:03:12,238
Hola, Mamá Coco.

43
00:03:13,049 --> 00:03:14,948
How are you, Julio?

44
00:03:15,439 --> 00:03:17,281
Actually, my name is Miguel.

45
00:03:17,554 --> 00:03:21,036
Mamá Coco has trouble remembering things.

46
00:03:21,342 --> 00:03:23,357
But it's good to talk to her anyway.

47
00:03:23,359 --> 00:03:25,366
So, I tell her pretty much everything.

48
00:03:25,414 --> 00:03:26,879
I used to run like this.

49
00:03:27,151 --> 00:03:29,567
But now I run like this which is way faster.

50
00:03:29,710 --> 00:03:31,265
And the winner is...

51
00:03:31,959 --> 00:03:33,581
Luchadora Coco!

52
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:36,386
I have a dimple on this side, but not on this side.

53
00:03:36,466 --> 00:03:38,343
Dimple, no dimple. Dimple, no dimple.

54
00:03:38,427 --> 00:03:40,555
Miguel, eat your food.

55
00:03:40,557 --> 00:03:41,737
My abuelita,

56
00:03:41,739 --> 00:03:43,186
she's Mamá Coco's daughter.

57
00:03:43,265 --> 00:03:45,286
Oh, you're a twig, mijo.

58
00:03:45,381 --> 00:03:47,277
Have some more. No, gracias.

59
00:03:47,602 --> 00:03:50,731
I asked if you would like more tamales!

60
00:03:50,897 --> 00:03:51,821
Sí?

61
00:03:52,107 --> 00:03:54,210
That's what I thought you said!

62
00:03:54,778 --> 00:03:58,142
Abuelita runs our house just like Mamá Imelda did.

63
00:04:00,949 --> 00:04:01,916
No music!

64
00:04:03,564 --> 00:04:04,691
No music!

65
00:04:04,786 --> 00:04:07,381
♪ Y aunque la vida ♪ No music!

66
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:11,548
I think we're the only family in México who hates music.

67
00:04:12,516 --> 00:04:14,037
And my family's fine with that.

68
00:04:14,243 --> 00:04:15,200
But me...

69
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:17,349
Be back by lunch, mijo. Love you, Mamá.

70
00:04:18,675 --> 00:04:21,019
I am not like the rest of my family!

71
00:04:22,561 --> 00:04:24,029
Hola, Miguel! Hola!

72
00:04:29,686 --> 00:04:31,859
Muchas gracias. De nada, Miguel.

73
00:04:36,777 --> 00:04:38,121
Hey! Dante!

74
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:41,614
Sit. Down.

75
00:04:42,080 --> 00:04:43,712
Roll over. Shake.

76
00:04:44,534 --> 00:04:45,351
Fist bump!

77
00:04:46,128 --> 00:04:47,628
Good boy, Dante!

78
00:04:51,345 --> 00:04:53,810
I know I'm not supposed to love music.

79
00:04:54,127 --> 00:04:55,621
But it's not my fault!

80
00:04:56,204 --> 00:04:57,305
It's his!

81
00:04:57,483 --> 00:04:59,560
Ernesto de la Cruz.

82
00:04:59,562 --> 00:05:02,229
The greatest musician of all time.

83
00:05:02,266 --> 00:05:04,358
Right here in this very plaza,

84
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:07,893
Ernesto de la Cruz took his first steps...

85
00:05:07,895 --> 00:05:11,709
toward becoming the most beloved singer in Méxican history.

86
00:05:12,187 --> 00:05:16,148
He started out a total nobody from Santa Cecilia, like me.

87
00:05:17,275 --> 00:05:18,863
But when he played music,

88
00:05:19,101 --> 00:05:21,247
he made people fall in love with him.

89
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:23,907
He starred in movies.

90
00:05:24,475 --> 00:05:26,269
He had the coolest guitar!

91
00:05:27,041 --> 00:05:28,250
He could fly!

92
00:05:28,701 --> 00:05:30,938
And he wrote the best songs.

93
00:05:31,206 --> 00:05:33,189
But my all-time favorite, it's...

94
00:05:33,667 --> 00:05:36,068
♪ Remember me ♪

95
00:05:36,923 --> 00:05:38,654
♪ Though I have to say goodbye ♪

96
00:05:38,656 --> 00:05:40,178
♪ Remember me ♪

97
00:05:40,715 --> 00:05:42,302
♪ Don't let it make you cry ♪

98
00:05:42,462 --> 00:05:44,359
♪ For even if I'm far away ♪

99
00:05:44,361 --> 00:05:45,878
♪ I hold you in my heart ♪

100
00:05:46,102 --> 00:05:48,012
♪ I sing a secret song to you ♪

101
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:49,491
♪ Each night we are apart ♪

102
00:05:49,493 --> 00:05:50,989
♪ Remember me ♪

103
00:05:51,154 --> 00:05:53,118
♪ Though I have to travel far ♪

104
00:05:53,142 --> 00:05:54,554
♪ Remember me ♪

105
00:05:54,883 --> 00:05:56,903
♪ Each time you hear a sad guitar ♪

106
00:05:57,248 --> 00:06:01,424
♪ Know that I'm with you the only way that I can be ♪

107
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:05,620
♪ Until you're in my arms again ♪

108
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:08,086
He lived the kind of life you dream about.

109
00:06:12,372 --> 00:06:13,965
Until 1942.

110
00:06:16,373 --> 00:06:19,105
When he was crushed by a giant bell.

111
00:06:20,304 --> 00:06:22,252
I want to be just like him.

112
00:06:28,555 --> 00:06:30,670
Sometimes, I look at de la Cruz

113
00:06:30,854 --> 00:06:32,480
and I get this feeling

114
00:06:32,890 --> 00:06:34,666
like we're connected somehow.

115
00:06:35,014 --> 00:06:36,944
Like if he could play music,

116
00:06:37,517 --> 00:06:39,655
maybe someday, I could too.

117
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:42,493
If it wasn't for my family.

118
00:06:42,691 --> 00:06:44,834
Ay-ay-ay, muchacho.

119
00:06:45,113 --> 00:06:47,405
I asked for a shoe shine not your life story.

120
00:06:47,407 --> 00:06:48,829
Oh, yeah. Sorry.

121
00:06:49,492 --> 00:06:52,667
I just can't really talk about any of this at home. So...

122
00:06:52,829 --> 00:06:54,011
Look if I were you,

123
00:06:54,013 --> 00:06:55,939
I'd march right up to my family and say...

124
00:06:55,941 --> 00:06:58,590
Hey, I'm a musician. Deal with it.

125
00:06:58,620 --> 00:07:00,158
I could never say that.

126
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:02,068
You are a musician, no?

127
00:07:02,212 --> 00:07:03,177
I don't know.

128
00:07:03,179 --> 00:07:06,049
I mean, I only really play for myself.

129
00:07:06,770 --> 00:07:11,038
Did de la Cruz become the world's best musician by hiding his skills?

130
00:07:11,170 --> 00:07:12,049
No!

131
00:07:12,051 --> 00:07:14,138
He walked out onto that plaza

132
00:07:14,140 --> 00:07:16,142
and he played out loud.

133
00:07:16,413 --> 00:07:18,361
Mira, mira, they're setting up for tonight!

134
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:21,098
The music competition for Día de Muertos.

135
00:07:21,307 --> 00:07:22,716
You want to be like your hero?

136
00:07:22,718 --> 00:07:23,811
You should sign up!

137
00:07:24,561 --> 00:07:26,177
My family would freak!

138
00:07:26,624 --> 00:07:28,790
Look, if you're too scared then, well...

139
00:07:28,792 --> 00:07:30,282
have fun making shoes.

140
00:07:31,228 --> 00:07:33,731
Come on, what did de la Cruz always say?

141
00:07:34,204 --> 00:07:35,917
Seize your moment?

142
00:07:37,165 --> 00:07:39,053
Show me what you got, muchacho.

143
00:07:40,543 --> 00:07:42,136
I'll be your first audience.

144
00:07:49,552 --> 00:07:50,394
Miguel!

145
00:07:52,591 --> 00:07:54,750
Abuelita! What are you doing here?

146
00:07:56,393 --> 00:07:58,020
You leave my grandson alone.

147
00:07:58,022 --> 00:07:59,123
Dona, please!

148
00:07:59,125 --> 00:08:00,214
I was just getting a shine.

149
00:08:00,397 --> 00:08:02,328
I know your tricks, mariachi.

150
00:08:02,330 --> 00:08:03,413
What did he say to you?

151
00:08:03,415 --> 00:08:04,961
He was just showing me his guitar.

152
00:08:05,587 --> 00:08:06,594
Shame on you.

153
00:08:06,945 --> 00:08:09,302
My grandson is a sweet little

154
00:08:09,304 --> 00:08:12,076
angelito querido cielito. Little darling angel

155
00:08:12,078 --> 00:08:14,920
He wants no part of your music, mariachi.

156
00:08:14,922 --> 00:08:16,424
You keep away from him.

157
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:21,695
Ay, pobrecito. Oh poor.

158
00:08:21,970 --> 00:08:23,782
Oh, estás bien, mijo. Oh you're fine, millet.

159
00:08:25,547 --> 00:08:27,675
You know better than to be here in this place!

160
00:08:28,499 --> 00:08:30,345
You will come home.

161
00:08:30,585 --> 00:08:31,357
Now.

162
00:08:41,688 --> 00:08:42,936
How many times have we told you?

163
00:08:42,938 --> 00:08:45,279
That plaza is crawling with mariachis.

164
00:08:45,281 --> 00:08:46,790
Yes, Tío Berto.

165
00:08:47,444 --> 00:08:48,492
No, no, no, no, no!

166
00:08:48,516 --> 00:08:50,544
Hey, go away, you. Go!

167
00:08:50,572 --> 00:08:51,744
It's just Dante.

168
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,813
Never name a street dog.

169
00:08:53,815 --> 00:08:55,286
They'll follow you forever.

170
00:08:55,779 --> 00:08:57,081
Now, go get my shoe.

171
00:09:03,162 --> 00:09:05,960
I found your son in Mariachi Plaza.

172
00:09:05,962 --> 00:09:07,260
Ay, Miguel!

173
00:09:07,297 --> 00:09:09,472
You know how Abuelita feels about the plaza.

174
00:09:09,591 --> 00:09:11,097
I was just shining shoes.

175
00:09:11,099 --> 00:09:12,394
A musician's shoes!

176
00:09:14,830 --> 00:09:16,774
But the plaza's where all the foot traffic is.

177
00:09:16,869 --> 00:09:18,784
If Abuelita says no more plaza,

178
00:09:18,865 --> 00:09:20,399
then no more plaza.

179
00:09:20,716 --> 00:09:22,691
But what about tonight? What's tonight?

180
00:09:22,890 --> 00:09:25,626
Well, they're having this talent show.

181
00:09:26,009 --> 00:09:27,472
And I thought I might...

182
00:09:27,734 --> 00:09:29,274
Sign up? Well...

183
00:09:29,744 --> 00:09:30,706
maybe?

184
00:09:31,027 --> 00:09:33,802
You have to have talent to be in a talent show.

185
00:09:33,818 --> 00:09:35,006
What are you gonna do?

186
00:09:35,008 --> 00:09:36,162
Shine shoes?

187
00:09:36,409 --> 00:09:38,081
It's Día de los Muertos.

188
00:09:38,161 --> 00:09:39,976
No one's going anywhere.

189
00:09:40,105 --> 00:09:41,636
Tonight is about family.

190
00:09:42,531 --> 00:09:44,340
Ofrenda room. Vámonos. Offering room. Let's go.

191
00:09:55,136 --> 00:09:56,809
Don't give me that look.

192
00:09:57,067 --> 00:09:59,806
Día de los Muertos is the one night of the year

193
00:09:59,808 --> 00:10:01,784
our ancestors can come visit us.

194
00:10:02,101 --> 00:10:04,057
We've put their photos on the ofrenda

195
00:10:04,059 --> 00:10:05,977
so their spirits can cross over.

196
00:10:06,212 --> 00:10:07,778
That is very important.

197
00:10:08,356 --> 00:10:09,569
If we don't put them up,

198
00:10:09,571 --> 00:10:10,674
they can't come.

199
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:12,467
We made all this food,

200
00:10:12,469 --> 00:10:15,213
set out the things they loved in life, mijo.

201
00:10:15,460 --> 00:10:18,598
All this work to bring the family together.

202
00:10:18,721 --> 00:10:21,457
I don't want you sneaking off to who knows where.

203
00:10:22,450 --> 00:10:23,591
Where are you going?

204
00:10:23,748 --> 00:10:24,794
I thought we were done.

205
00:10:24,874 --> 00:10:26,103
Ay, Dios mio. Oh Lord.

206
00:10:26,105 --> 00:10:29,798
Being part of this family means being here for this family.

207
00:10:29,834 --> 00:10:33,589
I don't want to see you end up like... Like Mamá Coco's Papá?

208
00:10:33,803 --> 00:10:35,489
Never mention that man!

209
00:10:35,491 --> 00:10:36,640
He's better off forgotten.

210
00:10:36,642 --> 00:10:37,535
But you're the one who...

211
00:10:38,061 --> 00:10:38,931
I was just...

212
00:10:39,192 --> 00:10:40,206
But... I...

213
00:10:40,908 --> 00:10:43,509
Papá? Papá is home?

214
00:10:43,643 --> 00:10:44,530
Mamá,

215
00:10:44,749 --> 00:10:46,484
cálmese, cálmese.

216
00:10:46,563 --> 00:10:48,220
Papá is coming home?

217
00:10:48,222 --> 00:10:49,328
No, Mamá.

218
00:10:49,449 --> 00:10:51,687
It's ok. I'm here.

219
00:10:52,569 --> 00:10:54,162
Who are you?

220
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:56,910
Rest, Mamá.

221
00:10:57,824 --> 00:11:00,554
I'm hard on you because I care, Miguel.

222
00:11:01,075 --> 00:11:01,925
Miguel?

223
00:11:02,546 --> 00:11:03,386
Miguel?

224
00:11:06,328 --> 00:11:08,401
What are we going to do with that boy?

225
00:11:10,266 --> 00:11:11,265
You're right.

226
00:11:11,267 --> 00:11:13,205
That's just what he needs.

227
00:11:37,743 --> 00:11:38,528
It's you.

228
00:11:38,530 --> 00:11:40,762
Get in here. Come on, Dante. Hurry up!

229
00:11:42,243 --> 00:11:44,328
You're gonna get me in trouble, boy.

230
00:11:44,551 --> 00:11:45,765
Someone could hear me.

231
00:11:50,460 --> 00:11:52,303
I wish someone wanted to hear me.

232
00:11:53,713 --> 00:11:54,860
Other than you.

233
00:11:58,968 --> 00:12:00,095
Perfecto!

234
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:34,934
I have to sing.

235
00:12:35,118 --> 00:12:36,481
I have to play!

236
00:12:36,622 --> 00:12:37,854
The music it's...

237
00:12:37,856 --> 00:12:39,216
it's not just in me,

238
00:12:39,828 --> 00:12:41,131
it is me.

239
00:12:42,845 --> 00:12:44,370
When life gets me down,

240
00:12:44,602 --> 00:12:45,875
I play my guitar.

241
00:12:46,933 --> 00:12:49,329
The rest of the world may follow the rules,

242
00:12:49,331 --> 00:12:51,790
but I must follow my heart.

243
00:12:53,690 --> 00:12:55,035
You know that feeling,

244
00:12:55,114 --> 00:12:58,504
like there is a song in the air and it's playing just for you?

245
00:13:02,525 --> 00:13:05,373
♪ A feeling so close ♪

246
00:13:05,399 --> 00:13:09,554
♪ You could reach out and touch it ♪

247
00:13:10,212 --> 00:13:16,284
♪ I never knew I could want something so much, but it's true ♪

248
00:13:17,297 --> 00:13:18,884
You must have faith, sister.

249
00:13:18,886 --> 00:13:21,340
Oh, but, Padre, he will never listen.

250
00:13:21,342 --> 00:13:23,319
He will listen. To music.

251
00:13:23,386 --> 00:13:26,488
♪ Only a song, only a song ♪

252
00:13:26,490 --> 00:13:29,908
♪ Has the power to change a heart ♪

253
00:13:33,765 --> 00:13:36,883
Never underestimate the power of music.

254
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:42,430
But my father,

255
00:13:42,587 --> 00:13:44,494
he will never give his permission.

256
00:13:44,574 --> 00:13:46,365
I am done asking permission.

257
00:13:46,422 --> 00:13:49,327
When you see your moment, you mustn't let it pass you by.

258
00:13:49,765 --> 00:13:51,152
You must seize it!

259
00:13:51,644 --> 00:13:52,955
Senor de la Cruz,

260
00:13:52,957 --> 00:13:55,386
what did it take for you to seize your moment?

261
00:13:57,086 --> 00:13:59,585
I had to have faith in my dream.

262
00:13:59,904 --> 00:14:01,773
No one was going to hand it to me.

263
00:14:01,775 --> 00:14:04,099
It was up to me to reach for that dream.

264
00:14:04,553 --> 00:14:05,715
Grab it tight,

265
00:14:05,999 --> 00:14:07,764
and make it come true. And make it come true.

266
00:14:12,550 --> 00:14:14,104
No more hiding, Dante.

267
00:14:14,267 --> 00:14:15,930
I got to seize my moment!

268
00:14:17,032 --> 00:14:20,155
I'm gonna play in Mariachi Plaza if it kills me.

269
00:14:24,034 --> 00:14:26,725
Día de los Muertos has begun!

270
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,774
No, no, no, no, no.

271
00:14:28,776 --> 00:14:30,518
We have to make a clear path.

272
00:14:30,591 --> 00:14:33,157
The petals guide our ancestors home.

273
00:14:33,159 --> 00:14:35,018
We don't want their spirits to get lost.

274
