389
00:21:53,854 --> 00:21:55,280
Alright, who's in there?

390
00:21:55,345 --> 00:21:56,357
I'm sorry.

391
00:21:56,359 --> 00:21:58,843
It's not what it looks like. De la Cruz is my...

392
00:22:00,754 --> 00:22:01,964
Nobody here.

393
00:22:17,753 --> 00:22:19,049
Miguel! Mamá!

394
00:22:19,129 --> 00:22:20,980
Miguel, come home.

395
00:22:22,171 --> 00:22:24,102
Where are you, Miguel?

396
00:22:27,012 --> 00:22:28,127
¡Dios mio! My god!

397
00:22:28,270 --> 00:22:30,224
Little boy. Are you ok?

398
00:22:30,472 --> 00:22:31,932
Here. Let me help you.

399
00:22:33,269 --> 00:22:34,450
Thanks. I...

400
00:22:45,281 --> 00:22:46,419
Do you mind?

401
00:23:07,845 --> 00:23:10,599
Look how big she's getting.

402
00:23:14,393 --> 00:23:15,269
Dante!

403
00:23:15,811 --> 00:23:17,087
You can see me?

404
00:23:17,865 --> 00:23:19,892
Wait! What's going on?

405
00:23:20,845 --> 00:23:22,510
Dante! Dante!

406
00:23:23,798 --> 00:23:25,290
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

407
00:23:25,321 --> 00:23:26,095
Miguel?

408
00:23:26,122 --> 00:23:27,446
Miguel? Miguel?

409
00:23:31,285 --> 00:23:32,381
You're here?

410
00:23:32,718 --> 00:23:34,790
Here, here. And you can see us?

411
00:23:34,792 --> 00:23:37,365
Our Migueli-ti-ti-ti-to!

412
00:23:37,379 --> 00:23:38,881
Remind me how I know you.

413
00:23:39,126 --> 00:23:41,003
We're your family, mijo.

414
00:23:43,143 --> 00:23:44,662
Tía Rosita?

415
00:23:44,997 --> 00:23:45,775
Sí.

416
00:23:47,676 --> 00:23:48,891
Papá Julio?

417
00:23:48,893 --> 00:23:49,680
Hola.

418
00:23:50,719 --> 00:23:52,380
Tía Victoria?

419
00:23:52,492 --> 00:23:54,671
He doesn't seem entirely dead.

420
00:23:55,267 --> 00:23:57,361
He's not quite alive either.

421
00:23:57,363 --> 00:23:58,736
We need Mamá Imelda.

422
00:23:58,738 --> 00:24:00,233
She'll know how to fix this.

423
00:24:00,235 --> 00:24:01,138
Oye!

424
00:24:02,557 --> 00:24:04,067
It's Mamá Imelda.

425
00:24:04,115 --> 00:24:05,541
She couldn't cross over.

426
00:24:05,616 --> 00:24:08,085
She's stuck! On the other side!

427
00:24:08,198 --> 00:24:09,227
Tío Oscar?

428
00:24:09,758 --> 00:24:10,784
Tío Felipe?

429
00:24:10,866 --> 00:24:11,845
Oh. Hey, Miguel.

430
00:24:12,701 --> 00:24:15,447
I have a feeling this has something to do with you.

431
00:24:15,449 --> 00:24:17,622
But if Mamá Imelda can't come to us...

432
00:24:17,624 --> 00:24:18,985
Then we are going to her.

433
00:24:19,201 --> 00:24:20,011
Vámonos! Let's go!

434
00:24:35,391 --> 00:24:36,352
Come on, Miguel.

435
00:24:36,679 --> 00:24:37,507
It's ok.

436
00:24:50,763 --> 00:24:51,513
Dante?

437
00:24:51,872 --> 00:24:52,628
Dante!

438
00:24:53,931 --> 00:24:55,092
Dante, wait up!

439
00:24:57,735 --> 00:24:59,354
You got to stay with me, boy.

440
00:24:59,474 --> 00:25:00,790
We don't know...

441
00:25:01,870 --> 00:25:02,697
where...

442
00:25:22,855 --> 00:25:24,322
This isn't a dream then.

443
00:25:24,646 --> 00:25:26,333
You're all really out there.

444
00:25:26,335 --> 00:25:28,296
You thought we weren't? Well, I don't know.

445
00:25:28,635 --> 00:25:29,643
I thought it might've been,

446
00:25:29,645 --> 00:25:32,027
one of those made up things that adults tell kids.

447
00:25:32,149 --> 00:25:33,391
Like vitamins.

448
00:25:33,493 --> 00:25:35,782
Miguel, vitamins are a real thing.

449
00:25:35,784 --> 00:25:37,377
Well, now I'm thinking maybe they could be.

450
00:25:38,287 --> 00:25:40,152
Mija, it's not nice to stare at...

451
00:25:40,154 --> 00:25:41,383
Ay! Santa Maria!

452
00:25:49,758 --> 00:25:50,827
Are those...

453
00:25:51,178 --> 00:25:52,322
Alebrijes!

454
00:25:52,899 --> 00:25:53,717
But those are...

455
00:25:53,719 --> 00:25:54,940
Real Alebrijes.

456
00:25:54,942 --> 00:25:56,227
Spirit creatures.

457
00:25:56,278 --> 00:25:58,145
They guide souls on their journey.

458
00:25:58,147 --> 00:26:00,349
Watch your step. They make caquitas everywhere.

459
00:26:00,601 --> 00:26:02,742
Welcome back to the Land of the Dead.

460
00:26:02,744 --> 00:26:05,483
Please have all offerings ready for re-entry.

461
00:26:05,485 --> 00:26:07,819
