00:42:41,597 --> 00:42:42,992
Nearly forgotten, you know?

815
00:42:43,144 --> 00:42:45,191
So, we all call each other cousin,

816
00:42:45,193 --> 00:42:47,241
or tío, or whatever.

817
00:42:52,415 --> 00:42:54,074
Héctor! Tía Chelo!

818
00:42:56,147 --> 00:42:57,833
Muchas gracias! Thank you very much!

819
00:42:57,835 --> 00:42:59,220
Hey! Save some for me!

820
00:42:59,333 --> 00:43:00,517
Is Chicharrón around?

821
00:43:00,610 --> 00:43:01,791
In the bungalow.

822
00:43:01,959 --> 00:43:04,569
I don't know if he's in the mood for visitors.

823
00:43:05,187 --> 00:43:07,664
Who doesn't like a visit from Cousin Héctor?

824
00:43:16,953 --> 00:43:18,626
Buenas noches, Chicharrón! Good evening, Chicharron!

825
00:43:18,628 --> 00:43:21,262
I don't want to see your stupid face, Héctor.

826
00:43:21,264 --> 00:43:23,279
Come on. It's Día de Muertos.

827
00:43:23,281 --> 00:43:24,832
I brought you a little offering.

828
00:43:24,834 --> 00:43:26,806
Get out of here. I would, Cheech.

829
00:43:26,854 --> 00:43:29,527
But the thing is, me and my friend, Miguel...

830
00:43:30,441 --> 00:43:32,239
We really need to borrow your guitar.

831
00:43:32,483 --> 00:43:33,926
My guitar? Yes.

832
00:43:33,928 --> 00:43:36,265
My prized beloved guitar?

833
00:43:36,267 --> 00:43:37,896
I promise we'll bring it right back.

834
00:43:37,898 --> 00:43:40,649
Like the time you promised to bring back my van?

835
00:43:40,651 --> 00:43:42,113
Or my mini-fridge?

836
00:43:42,548 --> 00:43:43,867
You see... Or my good napkins?

837
00:43:44,006 --> 00:43:45,633
My lasso? My femur?

838
00:43:45,665 --> 00:43:47,030
Well, no, not like those times.

839
00:43:47,032 --> 00:43:48,555
Where is my femur? You...

840
00:43:51,295 --> 00:43:52,804
You ok, amigo?

841
00:43:53,551 --> 00:43:55,383
I'm fading, Héctor.

842
00:43:55,716 --> 00:43:57,302
I can feel it.

843
00:43:58,248 --> 00:44:01,366
I couldn't even play that thing if I wanted to.

844
00:44:04,622 --> 00:44:07,146
You play me something.

845
00:44:07,163 --> 00:44:09,542
No. You know I don't play anymore, Cheech.

846
00:44:09,544 --> 00:44:10,839
The guitar is for the kid.

847
00:44:11,190 --> 00:44:12,575
You want it,

848
00:44:12,854 --> 00:44:14,847
you got to earn it.

849
00:44:16,404 --> 00:44:19,189
Ay, only for you, amigo.

850
00:44:21,742 --> 00:44:23,085
Any requests?

851
00:44:24,864 --> 00:44:27,151
You know my favorite, Héctor.

852
00:44:44,640 --> 00:44:48,152
♪ Well, everyone knows Juanita ♪

853
00:44:49,770 --> 00:44:52,774
♪ Her eyes each a different color ♪

854
00:44:54,609 --> 00:44:59,081
♪ Her teeth stick out and her chin goes in ♪

855
00:45:00,850 --> 00:45:02,858
♪ And her... ♪

856
00:45:04,139 --> 00:45:07,019
♪ Knuckles they drag on the floor ♪

857
00:45:07,021 --> 00:45:09,496
Those aren't the words. There are children present.

858
00:45:09,838 --> 00:45:13,388
♪ Her hair is like a briar ♪

859
00:45:14,503 --> 00:45:18,610
♪ She stands in a bow-legged stance ♪

860
00:45:20,134 --> 00:45:24,765
♪ And if I weren't so ugly ♪

861
00:45:26,064 --> 00:45:31,363
♪ She'd possibly give me a chance ♪

862
00:45:37,714 --> 00:45:39,500
Brings back memories.

863
00:45:44,200 --> 00:45:45,827
Gracias. Thank you.

864
00:46:17,161 --> 00:46:18,913
Wait. What happened?

865
00:46:19,604 --> 00:46:20,981
He's been forgotten.

866
00:46:21,607 --> 00:46:24,326
When there is no one left in the living world who remembers you...

867
00:46:24,407 --> 00:46:26,405
you disappear from this world.

868
00:46:27,222 --> 00:46:29,620
We call it the final death.

869
00:46:30,150 --> 00:46:32,244
Where did he go?

870
00:46:32,259 --> 00:46:33,720
No one knows.

871
00:46:33,959 --> 00:46:35,204
But I've met him.

872
00:46:35,206 --> 00:46:37,509
I could remember him when I go back!

873
00:46:37,670 --> 00:46:39,412
No, it doesn't work like that, chamaco.

874
00:46:40,089 --> 00:46:41,520
Our memories,

875
00:46:41,830 --> 00:46:44,882
they have to be passed down by those who knew us in life...

876
00:46:45,059 --> 00:46:47,562
in the stories they tell about us.

877
00:46:48,431 --> 00:46:51,294
But there is no one left alive to pass down Cheech's stories.

878
00:46:53,894 --> 00:46:55,825
Hey, it happens to everyone eventually.

879
00:46:56,105 --> 00:46:57,446
Come on de la Cruzcito,

880
00:46:57,710 --> 00:46:58,996
you've got a contest to win.

881
00:47:11,370 --> 00:47:13,389
You told me you hated musicians.

882
00:47:13,391 --> 00:47:14,875
You never said you were one.

883
00:47:14,877 --> 00:47:16,905
How do you think I knew your great-great-grandpa?

884
00:47:16,994 --> 00:47:18,478
We used to play music together.

885
00:47:18,480 --> 00:47:19,783
Taught him everything he knows.

886
00:47:20,214 --> 00:47:21,604
No manches!

887
00:47:21,606 --> 00:47:23,514
You played with Ernesto de la Cruz.

888
00:47:23,523 --> 00:47:25,241
The greatest musician of all time?

889
00:47:26,427 --> 00:47:27,351
You're funny.

890
00:47:27,353 --> 00:47:29,934
Greatest eyebrows of all time maybe, but his music?

891
00:47:30,094 --> 00:47:31,307
Hey not so much.

892
00:47:31,326 --> 00:47:33,077
You don't know what you're talking about.

893
00:47:35,436 --> 00:47:38,091
Welcome to the Plaza de la Cruz!

894
00:47:39,138 --> 00:47:40,856
Showtime, chamaco!

895
00:47:47,041 --> 00:47:49,663
Llévelo! T-shirts! Bobbleheads!

896
00:47:55,998 --> 00:47:59,719
Bienvenidos a todos! Welcome everybody!

897
00:48:01,921 --> 00:48:05,300
Who's ready for some música?

898
00:48:06,384 --> 00:48:08,762
It's a battle of the bands, amigos.

899
00:48:09,136 --> 00:48:11,865
The winner gets to play for the maestro himself,

900
00:48:12,041 --> 00:48:14,045
Ernesto de la Cruz,

901
00:48:14,047 --> 00:48:16,391
at his fiesta tonight!

902
00:48:17,061 --> 00:48:18,608
That's our ticket, muchacho.

903
00:48:20,606 --> 00:48:24,398
Let the competition begin!

904
00:48:40,167 --> 00:48:41,905
So, what's the plan? What are you gonna play?

905
00:48:42,062 --> 00:48:43,255
Definitely Remember Me.

906
00:48:43,680 --> 00:48:45,363
No! Not that one. No. Come on.

907
00:48:45,365 --> 00:48:46,930
It's his most popular song!

908
00:48:47,091 --> 00:48:48,133
It's too popular.

909
00:48:48,135 --> 00:48:50,058
♪ Remember me ♪ ♪ Though I have to travel far ♪

910
00:48:50,060 --> 00:48:53,944
♪ Remember me ♪ ♪ Don't let it make you cry ♪

911
00:48:58,092 --> 00:48:59,422
What about Poco Loco?

912
00:48:59,424 --> 00:49:01,475
Epa! Now that's a song!

913
00:49:01,530 --> 00:49:02,543
De la Cruzcito?

914
00:49:02,545 --> 00:49:03,514
You're on standby.

915
00:49:03,516 --> 00:49:05,217
Los Chachalacos, you're up next.

916
00:49:07,027 --> 00:49:08,567
Los Chachalacos!

917
00:49:19,957 --> 00:49:21,800
You always this nervous before a performance?

918
00:49:21,802 --> 00:49:22,736
I don't know.

919
00:49:22,738 --> 00:49:24,977
I've never performed before.

920
00:49:24,979 --> 00:49:26,943
What? You said you were a musician!

921
00:49:26,945 --> 00:49:28,881
I am! I mean, I will be.

922
00:49:28,883 --> 00:49:30,284
Ay! Once I win.

923
00:49:30,286 --> 00:49:31,528
That's your plan?

924
00:49:31,530 --> 00:49:33,210
No, no, no, no. You have to win, Miguel.

925
00:49:33,212 --> 00:49:35,160
Your life literally depends on you winning.

926
00:49:35,162 --> 00:49:36,721
And you've never done this before!

927
00:49:36,723 --> 00:49:37,890
I'll go up there. No!

928
00:49:37,892 --> 00:49:39,645
I need to do this. Why?

929
00:49:39,946 --> 00:49:42,065
If I can't go out and play one song,

930
00:49:42,120 --> 00:49:43,862
how can I call myself a musician?

931
00:49:43,879 --> 00:49:44,905
What does that matter?

932
00:49:44,907 --> 00:49:47,304
Because I don't just want to get de la Cruz's blessing...

933
00:49:47,757 --> 00:49:49,355
I need to prove that...

934
00:49:50,100 --> 00:49:51,604
I'm worthy of it.

935
00:49:52,625 --> 00:49:54,373
That's such a sweet sentiment,

936
00:49:54,684 --> 00:49:57,009
at such a bad time!

937
00:49:58,849 --> 00:50:00,113
Ok! Ok, ok.

938
00:50:00,115 --> 00:50:03,549
Ok. Ok you want to perform? Then you got to perform!

939
00:50:03,763 --> 00:50:06,429
First, you have to loosen up. Shake off those nerves.

940
00:50:10,709 --> 00:50:12,226
Now give me your best grito.

941
00:50:12,305 --> 00:50:13,463
My best grito?

942
00:50:13,465 --> 00:50:15,018
Come on, yell! Belt it out.

943
00:50:19,395 --> 00:50:21,546
It feels good. Ok, now, now you.

944
00:50:27,440 --> 00:50:28,559
Come on, kid.

945
00:50:39,286 --> 00:50:41,150
De la Cruzcito, you're on now!

946
00:50:41,152 --> 00:50:43,660
Miguel, look at me. Hey, hey look at me.

947
00:50:43,662 --> 00:50:44,908
Come on, let's go! You can do this.

948
00:50:45,274 --> 00:50:47,155
Grab their attention and don't let it go.

949
00:50:47,314 --> 00:50:49,544
Make them listen, chamaco. You've got this.

950
00:50:49,630 --> 00:50:51,758
De la Cruzcito!

951
00:50:51,958 --> 00:50:54,867
Arriba-Ba! Hey!

952
00:51:00,767 --> 00:51:02,770
What's he doing? Why isn't he playing?

953
00:51:03,573 --> 00:51:05,647
Bring back the singing dogs!

954
00:51:17,939 --> 00:51:20,186
Qué bien! Vámonos! How good! Let's go!

955
00:51:28,294 --> 00:51:31,798
♪ What color is the sky ♪ ♪ Ay mi amor, ay mi amor ♪

956
00:51:31,964 --> 00:51:35,594
♪ You tell me that it's red ♪ ♪ Ay mi amor, ay mi amor ♪

957
00:51:35,853 --> 00:51:39,348
♪ Where should I put my shoes ♪ ♪ Ay mi amor, ay mi amor ♪

958
00:51:39,377 --> 00:51:41,557
♪ You say put them on your head ♪

959
00:51:41,559 --> 00:51:44,224
♪ Ay mi amor, ay mi amor ♪

960
00:51:44,353 --> 00:51:48,825
♪ You make me un poco loco ♪ ♪ Un poqui-ti-ti-to loco ♪

961
00:51:48,887 --> 00:51:52,437
♪ The way you keep me guessing ♪ ♪ I'm nodding and I'm yes-ing ♪

962
00:51:52,485 --> 00:51:55,120
♪ I'll count it as a blessing ♪

963
00:51:55,363 --> 00:52:00,084
♪ That I'm only un poco loco ♪

964
00:52:00,701 --> 00:52:02,203
No! No! No!

965
00:52:08,876 --> 00:52:12,052
Not bad for a dead guy! Not so bad yourself, gordito!

966
00:52:12,070 --> 00:52:12,992
Eso!

967
00:52:20,220 --> 00:52:21,767
He's close! Find him!

968
00:52:22,071 --> 00:52:25,832
♪ The loco that you make me ♪ ♪ It is just un poco crazy ♪

969
00:52:25,851 --> 00:52:27,684
♪ The sense that you're not making ♪

970
00:52:27,686 --> 00:52:29,852
♪ The liberties you're taking ♪

971
00:52:29,854 --> 00:52:32,173
♪ Leaves my cabeza shaking ♪

972
00:52:32,332 --> 00:52:38,018
♪ You're just un poco locoooooo ♪

973
00:52:38,020 --> 00:52:39,487
Numero uno, Miguelito!

974
00:52:45,162 --> 00:52:47,844
We're looking for a living kid. About twelve?

975
00:52:47,915 --> 00:52:49,871
Have you seen a living boy?

976
00:52:50,584 --> 00:52:58,652
♪ Un poqui-ti-ti-ti-ti-ti-ti-ti-ti-ti-to locooooo ♪

977
00:53:04,056 --> 00:53:05,411
Hey! You did good!

978
00:53:05,821 --> 00:53:07,068
I'm proud of you.

979
00:53:07,658 --> 00:53:08,737
Eso! That's!

980
00:53:11,656 --> 00:53:14,160
¡Otra! ¡Otra! ¡Otra! Again! Again! Again!

981
00:53:18,404 --> 00:53:20,618
Hey! Where are you going? We got to get out of here!

982
00:53:20,620 --> 00:53:22,992
What? Are you crazy? We're about to win this thing.

983
00:53:24,284 --> 00:53:25,771
Damas y caballeros. Ladies and gentlemen.

984
00:53:25,820 --> 00:53:27,836
I have an emergency announcement.

985
00:53:27,955 --> 00:53:31,219
Please be on the lookout for a living boy.

986
00:53:31,524 --> 00:53:33,379
Answers to the name of Miguel.

987
00:53:33,460 --> 00:53:36,824
Earlier tonight he ran away from his family.

988
00:53:37,089 --> 00:53:39,927
They just want to send him back to the Land of the Living.

989
00:53:40,089 --> 00:53:41,033
Wait, wait, wait.

990
00:53:41,243 --> 00:53:43,218
You said de la Cruz was your only family.

991
00:53:43,220 --> 00:53:44,972
The only person who could send you home.

992
00:53:44,974 --> 00:53:46,415
I do have other family but...

993
00:53:46,417 --> 00:53:48,182
You could have taken my photo back this whole time?

994
00:53:48,184 --> 00:53:49,447
But they hate music!

995
00:53:49,449 --> 00:53:51,243
I need a musician's blessing.

996
00:53:51,311 --> 00:53:53,663
You lied to me! You're one to talk.

997
00:53:53,735 --> 00:53:55,814
Look at me. I'm being forgotten, Miguel.

998
00:53:55,816 --> 00:53:57,671
I don't even know if I'm gonna last the night.

999
00:53:57,776 --> 00:54:00,152
I'm not gonna miss my one chance to cross that bridge

1000
00:54:00,154 --> 00:54:03,397
because you want to live out some stupid musical fantasy.

1001
00:54:03,414 --> 00:54:05,683
It's not stupid! I'm taking you to your family.

1002
00:54:05,743 --> 00:54:07,165
Let go of me! You'll thank me later.

1003
00:54:07,167 --> 00:54:09,852
You don't want to help me. You only care about yourself!

1004
00:54:10,494 --> 00:54:12,032
Keep your dumb photo.

1005
00:54:12,034 --> 00:54:13,641
No. No. Stay away from me!

1006
00:54:13,643 --> 00:54:14,543
No!

1007
00:54:16,170 --> 00:54:17,544
Hey, chamaco!

1008
00:54:18,386 --> 00:54:19,506
Where did you go?

1009
00:54:20,257 --> 00:54:20,996
Chamaco! Boy!

1010
00:54:21,656 --> 00:54:23,757
I'm sorry! Come back!

1011
00:54:33,687 --> 00:54:35,032
Dante, cállate! Dante, shut up!

1012
00:54:36,320 --> 00:54:38,114
No! Dante, stop it.

1013
00:54:38,275 --> 00:54:39,556
He can't help me.

1014
00:54:41,267 --> 00:54:42,812
Dante! Stop!

1015
00:54:43,155 --> 00:54:44,265
Stop it!

1016
00:54:44,267 --> 00:54:45,466
Leave me alone!

1017
00:54:45,532 --> 00:54:48,093
You're not a spirit guide. You're just a dumb dog!

1018
00:54:48,693 --> 00:54:49,940
Now get out of here!

1019
00:54:49,953 --> 00:54:50,971
It's him!

1020
00:54:51,440 --> 00:54:52,704
It's that living boy!

1021
00:54:52,706 --> 00:54:54,420
I heard about him. Look! He's alive!

1022
00:54:54,507 --> 00:54:55,884
He's alive. The boy is alive!

1023
00:55:06,220 --> 00:55:08,644
This nonsense ends now, Miguel!

1024
00:55:08,719 --> 00:55:11,393
I am giving you my blessing and you are going home.

1025
00:55:11,435 --> 00:55:13,061
I don't want your blessing!

1026
00:55:14,227 --> 00:55:15,748
Miguel, stop!

1027
00:55:18,232 --> 00:55:19,364
Come back!

1028
00:55:21,654 --> 00:55:22,415
Miguel!

1029
00:55:26,796 --> 00:55:28,924
I am trying to save your life!

1030
00:55:28,995 --> 00:55:30,212
You're ruining my life!

1031
00:55:30,447 --> 00:55:31,165
What?

1032
00:55:31,167 --> 00:55:33,088
Music's the only thing that makes me happy.

1033
00:55:33,519 --> 00:55:35,961
And you want to take it away.

1034
00:55:36,413 --> 00:55:37,918
You'll never understand.

1035
00:55:41,171 --> 00:55:45,847
♪ Y aunque la vida me cueste, Llorona ♪

1036
00:55:46,181 --> 00:55:49,764
♪ No dejaré de quererte ♪

1037
00:55:50,938 --> 00:55:53,142
I thought you hated music.

1038
00:55:54,029 --> 00:55:55,563
I loved it!

1039
00:55:56,555 --> 00:55:58,286
I remember that feeling...

1040
00:55:58,632 --> 00:56:00,733
when my husband would play,

1041
00:56:00,735 --> 00:56:02,128
and I would sing,

1042
00:56:02,515 --> 00:56:05,081
and nothing else mattered.

1043
00:56:06,196 --> 00:56:07,973
But when we had Coco,

1044
00:56:08,261 --> 00:56:10,280
suddenly there was something in my life

1045
00:56:10,282 --> 00:56:13,234
that mattered more than music.

1046
00:56:14,174 --> 00:56:16,537
I wanted to put down roots.

1047
00:56:17,249 --> 00:56:19,923
He wanted to play for the world.

1048
00:56:21,108 --> 00:56:24,473
We each made a sacrifice to get what we wanted.

1049
00:56:25,044 --> 00:56:26,884
Now you must make a choice.

1050
00:56:27,050 --> 00:56:29,804
But I don't want to pick sides!

1051
00:56:30,265 --> 00:56:31,969
Why can't you be on my side?

1052
00:56:32,700 --> 00:56:34,428
That's what family's supposed to do.

1053
00:56:34,968 --> 00:56:36,065
Support you.

1054
00:56:38,090 --> 00:56:39,673
But you never will.

1055
00:56:58,665 --> 00:57:01,467
Have a good time. Oh, how exciting!

1056
00:57:02,753 --> 00:57:03,789
Oh, El Santo.

1057
00:57:03,791 --> 00:57:05,740
I'm a big fan!

1058
00:57:06,139 --> 00:57:07,749
You mind if I...

1059
00:57:12,512 --> 00:57:14,101
Gracias, Senor. Thank you, sir.

1060
00:57:17,851 --> 00:57:19,649
Invitation? It's ok.

1061
00:57:19,660 --> 00:57:22,222
I'm Ernesto's great-great-grandson.

1062
00:57:33,283 --> 00:57:34,432
Disculpen, senores. Excuse me, gentlemen.

1063
00:57:34,434 --> 00:57:36,646
Hey, guys! It's poco loco!

1064
00:57:36,648 --> 00:57:39,106
You were on fire tonight! You too!

1065
00:57:39,206 --> 00:57:41,199
Hey, musician to musician.

1066
00:57:41,422 --> 00:57:42,769
I need a favor.

1067
00:57:45,702 --> 00:57:47,214
The competition winners.

1068
00:57:47,216 --> 00:57:49,055
Congratulations, chicos.

1069
00:57:59,851 --> 00:58:00,898
Thanks, guys!

1070
00:58:13,490 --> 00:58:15,679
Hey! Enjoy the party, little músico!

1071
00:58:15,681 --> 00:58:16,540
Gracias! Thank you!

1072
00:58:31,883 --> 00:58:33,601
Look! It's Ernesto!

1073
00:58:35,654 --> 00:58:36,621
De la Cruz!

1074
00:58:37,764 --> 00:58:39,690
Senor de la Cruz!

1075
00:58:41,731 --> 00:58:42,643
Pardon me!

1076
00:58:43,130 --> 00:58:45,402
Senor de la Cruz! Senor de la...

1077
00:58:50,944 --> 00:58:53,948
When you see your moment, you mustn't let it pass you by.

1078
00:58:54,114 --> 00:58:55,787
You must seize it.

1079
00:58:55,949 --> 00:58:57,952
This one has a wise spirit.

1080
00:59:12,758 --> 00:59:14,135
We're almost there, Dante.

1081
00:59:18,472 --> 00:59:19,676
Senor de la Cruz!

1082
00:59:20,066 --> 00:59:21,244
Senor de la...

1083
00:59:26,709 --> 00:59:28,218
But what can we do?

1084
00:59:28,220 --> 00:59:29,404
It is hopeless...

1085
00:59:29,483 --> 00:59:31,168
You must have faith, sister.

1086
00:59:31,170 --> 00:59:33,294
But Padre, he will never listen.

1087
00:59:33,320 --> 00:59:35,869
He will listen, to music.

1088
01:00:00,472 --> 01:00:04,978
♪ Señoras y senores, buenas tardes ♪ ♪ buenas noches ♪

1089
01:00:05,102 --> 01:00:09,152
♪ Buenas tardes, buenas noches ♪ ♪ Senoritas y senores ♪

1090
01:00:09,173 --> 01:00:13,391
♪ To be here with you tonight ♪ ♪ Brings me joy! Qué alegría ♪

1091
01:00:13,393 --> 01:00:18,982
♪ For this music is my language ♪ And the world es mi familia ♪

1092
01:00:19,757 --> 01:00:24,512
♪ For this music is my language ♪ And the world es mi familia ♪

1093
01:00:24,877 --> 01:00:30,966
♪ For this music is my language ♪ And the world es mi familia ♪

1094
01:00:31,128 --> 01:00:32,755
♪ For this music is my lang... ♪

1095
01:00:45,225 --> 01:00:46,551
Are you alright, nino?

1096
01:00:50,897 --> 01:00:52,094
It's. It's you!

1097
01:00:52,616 --> 01:00:55,904
You are that boy! The one who came from the Land of the Living.

1098
01:00:56,069 --> 01:00:58,059
You... know about me?

1099
01:00:58,155 --> 01:01:01,068
You are all anyone has been talking about.

1100
01:01:01,762 --> 01:01:03,213
Why have you come here?

1101
01:01:03,702 --> 01:01:04,887
I'm Miguel.

1102
01:01:05,555 --> 01:01:08,173
Your great-great-grandson.

1103
01:01:09,249 --> 01:01:11,553
I... have a great-great-grandson?

1104
01:01:11,597 --> 01:01:12,793
I need your blessing,

1105
01:01:13,301 --> 01:01:15,676
so I can go back home and be a musician.

1106
01:01:15,755 --> 01:01:16,631
Just like you.

1107
01:01:17,401 --> 01:01:18,969
The rest of our family,

1108
01:01:19,678 --> 01:01:20,919
they would not listen.

1109
01:01:21,505 --> 01:01:24,018
But I hoped you would.

1110
01:01:26,016 --> 01:01:28,668
My boy, with a talent like yours,

1111
01:01:29,349 --> 01:01:30,655
how could I not listen?

1112
01:01:33,732 --> 01:01:36,030
I have a great-great-grandson!

1113
01:01:42,782 --> 01:01:45,369
Look! It's Frida! Yes, it is I.

1114
01:01:45,371 --> 01:01:46,321
Frida Kahlo.

1115
01:01:46,323 --> 01:01:48,789
It is an honor, señora. Gracias.

1116
01:01:53,460 --> 01:01:55,339
Hey, Negrete! Infante!

1117
01:01:55,341 --> 01:01:57,136
Have you met my great-great-grandson?

1118
01:01:57,714 --> 01:01:59,387
My great-great-grandson.

1119
01:01:59,507 --> 01:02:01,889
He's alive! And a musician to boot!

1120
01:02:02,070 --> 01:02:03,804
Dimple. No dimple. Dimple. No dimple.

1121
01:02:03,929 --> 01:02:04,976
No dimple!

1122
01:02:05,048 --> 01:02:06,345
To our friendship.

1123
01:02:06,917 --> 01:02:09,597
I would move Heaven and Earth for you, mi amigo.

1124
01:02:09,599 --> 01:02:10,486
Salud! Cheers!

1125
01:02:11,895 --> 01:02:12,920
Poison!

1126
01:02:13,480 --> 01:02:15,608
You know, I did all my own stunts.

1127
01:02:15,732 --> 01:02:19,407
♪ Though I have to say goodbye ♪ ♪ Remember me... ♪

1128
01:02:21,279 --> 01:02:25,338
All of this came from my amazing fans in the Land of the Living.

1129
01:02:26,576 --> 01:02:29,851
They leave me more offerings than I know what to do with!

1130
01:02:30,664 --> 01:02:31,942
Hey, what's wrong?

1131
01:02:31,944 --> 01:02:33,859
Is it too much? You look overwhelmed.

1132
01:02:33,861 --> 01:02:36,525
No! It's all great!

1133
01:02:36,527 --> 01:02:37,445
But?

1134
01:02:37,462 --> 01:02:38,575
It's just...

1135
01:02:39,021 --> 01:02:42,037
I have been looking up to you my whole life.

1136
01:02:42,273 --> 01:02:45,283
You're the guy who actually did it!

1137
01:02:46,263 --> 01:02:48,539
But did you ever regret it?

1138
01:02:48,926 --> 01:02:52,302
Choosing music over everything else?

1139
01:02:52,978 --> 01:02:54,235
It was hard.

1140
01:02:54,455 --> 01:02:56,709
Saying goodbye to my hometown.

1141
01:02:57,131 --> 01:02:58,657
Heading off on my own...

1142
01:02:59,651 --> 01:03:01,166
Leaving your family?

1143
01:03:01,695 --> 01:03:02,523
Sí.

1144
01:03:03,217 --> 01:03:05,939
But I could not have done it differently.

1145
01:03:06,690 --> 01:03:09,378
One cannot deny who one is meant to be.

1146
01:03:10,036 --> 01:03:12,221
And you, my great-great-grandson,

1147
01:03:12,223 --> 01:03:14,167
are meant to be a musician!

1148
01:03:16,710 --> 01:03:19,351
You and I, we are artists, Miguel.

1149
01:03:19,353 --> 01:03:21,369
We cannot belong to one family.

1150
01:03:21,693 --> 01:03:23,946
The world is our family.

1151
01:03:26,546 --> 01:03:28,127
The fireworks have begun!

1152
01:03:38,565 --> 01:03:42,292
Soon the party will move across town for my Sunrise Spectacular.

1153
01:03:43,361 --> 01:03:45,759
Miguel, you must come to the show!

1154
01:03:45,761 --> 01:03:47,824
You will be my guest of honor!

1155
01:03:47,826 --> 01:03:50,115
You mean it? Of course, my boy.

1156
01:03:52,662 --> 01:03:53,963
I can't.

1157
01:03:54,352 --> 01:03:56,668
I have to get home before sunrise.

1158
01:03:57,230 --> 01:03:59,119
I really do need to get you home.

1159
01:04:03,256 --> 01:04:05,402
It has been an honor.

1160
01:04:05,948 --> 01:04:08,190
I am sorry to see you go, Miguel.

1161
01:04:08,366 --> 01:04:10,332
I hope you die very soon.

1162
01:04:12,818 --> 01:04:14,240
You know what I mean.

1163
01:04:16,409 --> 01:04:17,310
Miguel,

1164
01:04:17,903 --> 01:04:20,908
I give you my bless... We had a deal, chamaco.

1165
01:04:21,524 --> 01:04:22,739
Who are you?

1166
01:04:22,741 --> 01:04:24,279
What is the meaning of this?

1167
01:04:25,658 --> 01:04:26,553
Frida!

1168
01:04:26,650 --> 01:04:27,906
I thought you couldn't make it.

1169
01:04:28,448 --> 01:04:30,295
You said you'd take back my photo.

1170
01:04:30,297 --> 01:04:31,403
You promised, Miguel.

1171
01:04:31,409 --> 01:04:33,441
You know this man?

1172
01:04:33,453 --> 01:04:35,345
I just met him tonight.

1173
01:04:35,347 --> 01:04:37,046
He told me he knew you.

1174
01:04:37,764 --> 01:04:38,488
Hé...

1175
01:04:38,942 --> 01:04:39,662
Héctor?

1176
01:04:39,664 --> 01:04:40,704
Please, Miguel.

1177
01:04:41,211 --> 01:04:42,589
Put my photo up.

1178
01:04:44,422 --> 01:04:45,529
My friend,

1179
01:04:45,932 --> 01:04:47,004
you're...

1180
01:04:47,375 --> 01:04:48,481
you're being forgotten.

1181
01:04:48,483 --> 01:04:49,590
And whose fault is that?

1182
01:04:49,592 --> 01:04:50,418
Héctor, please...

1183
01:04:50,420 --> 01:04:51,680
Those were my songs you took.

1184
01:04:51,682 --> 01:04:53,573
My songs that made you famous.

1185
01:04:53,640 --> 01:04:55,145
What? If I'm being forgotten,

1186
01:04:55,147 --> 01:04:57,583
it's because you never told anyone that I wrote them!

1187
01:04:57,585 --> 01:04:58,483
That's crazy!

1188
01:04:58,587 --> 01:05:00,997
De la Cruz wrote all his own songs.

1189
01:05:01,231 --> 01:05:02,669
You want to tell him or should I?

1190
01:05:02,671 --> 01:05:03,498
Héctor,

1191
01:05:03,500 --> 01:05:05,535
I never meant to take credit.

1192
01:05:05,537 --> 01:05:07,579
We made a great team but,

1193
01:05:07,659 --> 01:05:09,148
you died...

1194
01:05:09,312 --> 01:05:11,659
and I only sang your songs because

1195
01:05:11,810 --> 01:05:14,261
I wanted to keep a part of you alive.

1196
01:05:14,363 --> 01:05:15,580
How generous!

1197
01:05:15,787 --> 01:05:17,794
You really did play together.

1198
01:05:17,796 --> 01:05:18,379
Look...

1199
01:05:18,921 --> 01:05:20,240
I don't want to fight about it.

1200
01:05:20,536 --> 01:05:22,133
I just want you to make it right.

1201
01:05:22,640 --> 01:05:24,155
Miguel can put my photo up,

1202
01:05:24,157 --> 01:05:26,069
Héctor. And I can cross over the bridge.

1203
01:05:26,756 --> 01:05:27,991
I can see my girl.

1204
01:05:28,869 --> 01:05:29,687
Ernesto,

1205
01:05:30,282 --> 01:05:31,663
remember the night I left?

1206
01:05:31,678 --> 01:05:33,177
That was a long time ago.

1207
01:05:33,179 --> 01:05:34,328
We drank together

1208
01:05:34,528 --> 01:05:37,489
and you told me you would move Heaven and Earth for your amigo.

1209
01:05:38,068 --> 01:05:38,852
Well,

1210
01:05:39,363 --> 01:05:40,697
I'm asking you to now.

1211
01:05:40,699 --> 01:05:41,844
Heaven and Earth?

1212
01:05:42,198 --> 01:05:43,271
Like in the movie?

1213
01:05:43,273 --> 01:05:43,801
What?

1214
01:05:44,012 --> 01:05:45,743
That's Don Hidalgo's toast.

1215
01:05:46,151 --> 01:05:48,323
In the de la Cruz movie, El Camino a Casa.

1216
01:05:48,325 --> 01:05:49,995
I'm talking about my real life, Miguel.

1217
01:05:49,997 --> 01:05:51,638
No! It's in there.

1218
01:05:51,679 --> 01:05:52,573
Look!

1219
01:05:52,644 --> 01:05:54,154
Never were truer words spoken.

1220
01:05:54,156 --> 01:05:56,607
This calls for a toast. To our friendship!

1221
01:05:57,465 --> 01:05:59,745
I would move Heaven and Earth for you, mi amigo.

1222
01:05:59,802 --> 01:06:00,858
But in the movie,

1223
01:06:00,860 --> 01:06:02,957
Don Hidalgo poisons the drink.

1224
01:06:03,103 --> 01:06:03,995
Salud! Cheers!

1225
01:06:05,050 --> 01:06:06,029
Poison!

1226
01:06:08,214 --> 01:06:09,879
That night, Ernesto.

1227
01:06:10,587 --> 01:06:11,866
The night I left...

1228
01:06:12,510 --> 01:06:14,813
We'd been performing on the road for months.

1229
01:06:15,303 --> 01:06:16,304
I got homesick...

1230
01:06:16,492 --> 01:06:17,884
and I packed up my songs.

1231
01:06:19,058 --> 01:06:22,560
You want to give up now when we're this close to reaching our dream?

1232
01:06:22,562 --> 01:06:23,568
This was your dream.

1233
01:06:23,673 --> 01:06:24,509
You'll manage.

1234
01:06:24,522 --> 01:06:26,426
I can't do this without your songs, Héctor.

1235
01:06:26,547 --> 01:06:30,222
I'm going home, Ernesto. Hate me if you want, but my mind is made up.

1236
01:06:33,907 --> 01:06:39,505
I could never hate you. If you must go, then I'm sending you off with a toast.

1237
01:06:43,291 --> 01:06:44,588
To our friendship.

1238
01:06:44,751 --> 01:06:48,927
I would move Heaven and Earth for you, mi amigo. Salud!

1239
01:06:54,010 --> 01:06:57,765
You walked me to the train station. But I felt a pain in my stomach.

1240
01:06:58,681 --> 01:07:00,274
I thought it must have been something I ate.

1241
01:07:00,433 --> 01:07:02,276
Perhaps it was that chorizo, my friend.

1242
01:07:02,936 --> 01:07:05,155
Or something I drank.

1243
01:07:08,775 --> 01:07:10,527
I woke up dead.

1244
01:07:12,445 --> 01:07:14,618
You poisoned me.

1245
01:07:14,781 --> 01:07:18,035
You're confusing movies with reality, Héctor.

1246
01:07:18,201 --> 01:07:21,455
All this time, I thought it was just bad luck.

1247
01:07:22,872 --> 01:07:24,924
I never thought that you might have...

1248
01:07:26,051 --> 01:07:26,996
That you...

1249
01:07:30,755 --> 01:07:32,348
How could you? Héctor!

1250
01:07:32,350 --> 01:07:33,702
Security! Security!

1251
01:07:34,801 --> 01:07:37,079
You took everything away from me!

1252
01:07:37,795 --> 01:07:38,664
You rat!

1253
01:07:39,889 --> 01:07:41,285
Have him taken care of.

1254
01:07:41,501 --> 01:07:42,683
He's not well.

1255
01:07:42,892 --> 01:07:44,864
I just wanted to go back home.

1256
01:07:45,168 --> 01:07:45,888
No!

1257
01:07:46,381 --> 01:07:47,487
No!

1258
01:07:49,065 --> 01:07:50,170
I apologize.

1259
01:07:51,209 --> 01:07:52,286
Where were we?

1260
01:07:52,652 --> 01:07:54,780
You were going to give me your blessing.

1261
01:07:54,946 --> 01:07:55,715
Yes.

1262
01:07:56,716 --> 01:07:57,497
Sí.

1263
01:08:00,034 --> 01:08:01,202
Miguel,

1264
01:08:01,690 --> 01:08:03,381
my reputation...

1265
01:08:03,496 --> 01:08:04,323
It is...

1266
01:08:05,379 --> 01:08:07,457
very important to me.

1267
01:08:07,872 --> 01:08:09,623
I would hate to have you think...

1268
01:08:09,625 --> 01:08:12,327
That you murdered Héctor,

1269
01:08:12,392 --> 01:08:13,501
for his songs?

1270
01:08:15,469 --> 01:08:17,068
You don't think that.

1271
01:08:17,653 --> 01:08:18,880
Do you? I...

1272
01:08:18,882 --> 01:08:19,928
No.

1273
01:08:20,103 --> 01:08:21,282
Everyone knows you're...

1274
01:08:21,641 --> 01:08:23,288
the good guy.

1275
01:08:29,689 --> 01:08:31,148
Papá Ernesto,

1276
01:08:31,268 --> 01:08:32,695
my blessing?

1277
01:08:34,861 --> 01:08:35,906
Security?

1278
01:08:36,344 --> 01:08:37,465
Take care of Miguel.

1279
01:08:37,467 --> 01:08:39,335
He'll be extending his stay.

1280
01:08:39,354 --> 01:08:40,047
What?

1281
01:08:41,128 --> 01:08:42,298
But I'm your family!

1282
01:08:42,300 --> 01:08:44,300
And Héctor was my best friend.

1283
01:08:45,204 --> 01:08:47,976
Success doesn't come for free, Miguel.

1284
01:08:48,333 --> 01:08:51,964
You have to be willing to do whatever it takes to...

1285
01:08:52,045 --> 01:08:53,419
seize your moment.

1286
01:08:54,339 --> 01:08:55,705
I know you understand.

1287
01:08:56,049 --> 01:08:58,143
No! No!

1288
01:09:00,219 --> 01:09:01,187
Let go!

1289
01:09:02,465 --> 01:09:03,099
No!

1290
01:09:03,382 --> 01:09:04,771
No!

1291
01:09:25,703 --> 01:09:26,566
Help!

1292
01:09:27,341 --> 01:09:28,718
Can anyone hear me?

1293
01:09:30,196 --> 01:09:31,996
I want to go home.

1294
01:09:50,730 --> 01:09:51,857
Héctor?

1295
01:09:52,200 --> 01:09:52,573
Kid?

1296
01:09:53,077 --> 01:09:53,870
Héctor!

1297
01:09:54,965 --> 01:09:55,862
You were right.

1298
01:09:55,872 --> 01:09:58,007
I should have gone back to my family.

1299
01:09:58,126 --> 01:10:00,909
They told me not to be like de la Cruz,

1300
01:10:01,236 --> 01:10:02,617
but I didn't listen.

1301
01:10:02,619 --> 01:10:05,464
I told them I didn't care if they remembered me.

1302
01:10:05,531 --> 01:10:08,410
I didn't care if I was on their stupid ofrenda.

1303
01:10:08,913 --> 01:10:09,915
Hey, chamaco.

1304
01:10:09,917 --> 01:10:11,749
It's ok. It's ok.

1305
01:10:11,822 --> 01:10:14,396
I told them I didn't care.

1306
01:10:18,297 --> 01:10:20,925
Héctor! Héctor?

1307
01:10:22,176 --> 01:10:23,007
She's...

1308
01:10:24,007 --> 01:10:25,191
forgetting me.

1309
01:10:25,722 --> 01:10:26,675
Who?

1310
01:10:27,462 --> 01:10:28,700
My daughter.

1311
01:10:30,951 --> 01:10:35,140
She's the reason you wanted to cross the bridge.

1312
01:10:35,898 --> 01:10:37,665
I just wanted to see her again.

1313
01:10:39,275 --> 01:10:41,473
I never should have left Santa Cezilia.

1314
01:10:42,947 --> 01:10:44,790
I wish I could apologize.

1315
01:10:45,029 --> 01:10:48,424
I wish I could tell her that her Papá was trying to come home.

1316
01:10:49,162 --> 01:10:51,290
That he loved her so much.

1317
01:10:53,666 --> 01:10:55,088
My Coco...

1318
01:10:57,837 --> 01:10:59,143
Coco?

1319
01:11:14,636 --> 01:11:15,596
Where...

1320
01:11:16,404 --> 01:11:17,820
did you get this?

1321
01:11:18,566 --> 01:11:20,443
That's my Mamá Coco.

1322
01:11:20,806 --> 01:11:22,492
That's my Mamá Imelda.

1323
01:11:23,529 --> 01:11:24,537
Is that...

1324
01:11:25,744 --> 01:11:26,681
you?

1325
01:11:30,203 --> 01:11:31,193
We're...

1326
01:11:32,544 --> 01:11:33,527
family?

1327
01:11:46,206 --> 01:11:48,730
I always hoped I'd see her again.

1328
01:11:49,634 --> 01:11:50,675
That she'd miss me.

1329
01:11:51,224 --> 01:11:52,622
Maybe put up my photo.

1330
01:11:53,652 --> 01:11:54,900
But it never happened.

1331
01:11:56,229 --> 01:11:57,526
You know the worst part?

1332
01:11:58,191 --> 01:12:00,738
Even if I never got to see Coco in the living world...

1333
01:12:01,166 --> 01:12:03,676
I thought at least one day I'd see her here.

1334
01:12:04,379 --> 01:12:05,924
Give her the biggest hug.

1335
01:12:08,157 --> 01:12:10,744
But she's the last person who remembers me.

1336
01:12:11,619 --> 01:12:13,792
The moment she's gone from the living world...

1337
01:12:14,018 --> 01:12:15,383
You disappear...

1338
01:12:16,065 --> 01:12:17,324
from this one.

1339
01:12:18,105 --> 01:12:19,847
You'll never get to see her.

1340
01:12:19,922 --> 01:12:21,177
Ever again.

1341
01:12:24,882 --> 01:12:25,595
You know,

1342
01:12:25,922 --> 01:12:27,382
I wrote her a song once.

1343
01:12:28,094 --> 01:12:29,887
We used to sing it every night,

1344
01:12:30,238 --> 01:12:31,564
at the same time.

1345
01:12:32,181 --> 01:12:34,434
No matter how far apart we were.

1346
01:12:35,768 --> 01:12:37,871
What I would not give to sing it to her,

1347
01:12:38,401 --> 01:12:39,061
one...

1348
01:12:39,341 --> 01:12:40,127
last...

1349
