♪ Remember... ♪

1364
01:13:41,508 --> 01:13:45,367
♪ Me ♪

1365
01:13:48,466 --> 01:13:49,875
He stole your guitar.

1366
01:13:50,147 --> 01:13:51,803
He stole your songs.

1367
01:13:52,511 --> 01:13:54,761
You should be the one the world remembers,

1368
01:13:54,763 --> 01:13:56,016
not de la Cruz!

1369
01:13:56,086 --> 01:13:57,947
I didn't write Remember Me for the world.

1370
01:13:58,862 --> 01:14:00,728
I wrote it for Coco.

1371
01:14:02,342 --> 01:14:04,878
I'm a pretty sorry excuse for a great-great-grandpa.

1372
01:14:05,148 --> 01:14:05,968
Are you kidding?

1373
01:14:05,970 --> 01:14:08,558
A minute ago I thought I was related to a murderer.

1374
01:14:08,861 --> 01:14:10,203
You're a total upgrade.

1375
01:14:11,110 --> 01:14:12,365
My whole life,

1376
01:14:12,524 --> 01:14:14,967
there is been something that made me different.

1377
01:14:15,488 --> 01:14:17,422
And I never knew where it came from.

1378
01:14:18,079 --> 01:14:19,253
But now I know.

1379
01:14:19,381 --> 01:14:21,101
It comes from you.

1380
01:14:21,832 --> 01:14:23,543
I'm proud we're family!

1381
01:14:24,631 --> 01:14:27,010
I'm proud to be his family!

1382
01:14:34,053 --> 01:14:36,550
I'm proud to be his family!

1383
01:14:51,864 --> 01:14:52,776
Dante?

1384
01:14:55,241 --> 01:14:56,150
Dante!

1385
01:14:58,744 --> 01:14:59,959
It's Dante!

1386
01:15:11,507 --> 01:15:12,485
Imelda!

1387
01:15:13,432 --> 01:15:14,626
Héctor.

1388
01:15:15,436 --> 01:15:16,645
You look good.

1389
01:15:28,242 --> 01:15:31,417
Dante! You knew he was my Papá Héctor the whole time!

1390
01:15:31,444 --> 01:15:33,519
You are a real spirit guide.

1391
01:15:33,529 --> 01:15:35,307
Who's the good spirit guide?

1392
01:15:35,309 --> 01:15:36,230
You are!

1393
01:15:56,052 --> 01:15:56,952
Dante!

1394
01:16:21,077 --> 01:16:22,057
There they are!

1395
01:16:22,161 --> 01:16:23,282
Miguel! Miguelito!

1396
01:16:23,363 --> 01:16:24,697
Look, it's Miguel!

1397
01:16:25,482 --> 01:16:26,552
He's alright.

1398
01:16:27,218 --> 01:16:28,586
Gracias, Dios mío. Thank, my God.

1399
01:16:29,524 --> 01:16:30,678
Qué bueno. That good.

1400
01:16:45,267 --> 01:16:47,374
Mijo, I was so worried!

1401
01:16:47,376 --> 01:16:49,627
Thank goodness we found you in time.

1402
01:16:50,523 --> 01:16:51,427
And you...

1403
01:16:51,918 --> 01:16:54,246
How many times must I turn you away?

1404
01:16:54,301 --> 01:16:54,941
Imelda.

1405
01:16:54,943 --> 01:16:56,650
I want nothing to do with you!

1406
01:16:56,652 --> 01:16:58,529
Not in life, not in death!

1407
01:16:58,779 --> 01:17:02,001
I spent decades protecting my family from your mistakes.

1408
01:17:02,118 --> 01:17:05,856
He spends five minutes with you and I have to fish him out of a sinkhole!

1409
01:17:05,858 --> 01:17:07,450
I wasn't in there because of Héctor.

1410
01:17:07,685 --> 01:17:09,311
He was in there because of me.

1411
01:17:10,126 --> 01:17:12,383
He was just trying to get me home!

1412
01:17:12,545 --> 01:17:14,101
I didn't want to listen,

1413
01:17:14,457 --> 01:17:15,872
but he was right.

1414
01:17:16,674 --> 01:17:18,551
Nothing's more important than family.

1415
01:17:20,219 --> 01:17:22,729
I'm ready to accept your blessing.

1416
01:17:23,055 --> 01:17:24,714
And your conditions.

1417
01:17:25,187 --> 01:17:27,408
But first, I need to find de la Cruz.

1418
01:17:27,828 --> 01:17:29,505
To get Héctor's photo. What?

1419
01:17:29,507 --> 01:17:30,933
So he can see Coco again.

1420
01:17:30,987 --> 01:17:32,993
Héctor should be on our ofrenda.

1421
01:17:32,995 --> 01:17:34,302
He's part of our family.

1422
01:17:34,304 --> 01:17:35,732
He left this family!

1423
01:17:35,734 --> 01:17:37,631
He tried to go home to you and Coco.

1424
01:17:37,633 --> 01:17:39,532
But de la Cruz murdered him!

1425
01:17:40,531 --> 01:17:41,995
It's true, Imelda.

1426
01:17:42,983 --> 01:17:44,567
And so what if it's true?

1427
01:17:44,727 --> 01:17:46,900
You leave me alone with a child to raise...

1428
01:17:46,912 --> 01:17:49,008
and I'm just supposed to forgive you?

1429
01:17:49,081 --> 01:17:50,082
Imelda, I...

1430
01:17:51,041 --> 01:17:52,293
Héctor!

1431
01:17:55,242 --> 01:17:56,661
I'm running out of time.

1432
01:17:57,881 --> 01:17:58,859
It's Coco.

1433
01:17:59,826 --> 01:18:01,319
She's forgetting you.

1434
01:18:02,511 --> 01:18:04,499
You don't have to forgive him.

1435
01:18:05,123 --> 01:18:07,627
But we should not forget him.

1436
01:18:10,319 --> 01:18:12,668
I wanted to forget you.

1437
01:18:13,439 --> 01:18:16,193
I wanted Coco to forget you too, but...

1438
01:18:16,195 --> 01:18:17,383
This is my fault.

1439
01:18:18,366 --> 01:18:19,368
Not yours.

1440
01:18:21,363 --> 01:18:23,161
I'm sorry, Imelda.

1441
01:18:27,453 --> 01:18:28,724
Miguel,

1442
01:18:29,197 --> 01:18:31,217
if we help you get his photo,

1443
01:18:31,560 --> 01:18:32,927
you will return home?

1444
01:18:33,148 --> 01:18:34,149
No more music?

1445
01:18:35,461 --> 01:18:37,759
Family comes first.

1446
01:18:40,132 --> 01:18:40,988
I...

1447
01:18:41,497 --> 01:18:43,253
I can't forgive you.

1448
01:18:45,429 --> 01:18:46,976
But I will help you.

1449
01:18:48,981 --> 01:18:51,352
So, how do we get to de la Cruz?

1450
01:18:52,394 --> 01:18:54,772
I might know a way.

1451
01:19:45,531 --> 01:19:47,711
Good luck, muchacho. Gracias, Frida.

1452
01:19:56,625 --> 01:19:58,377
Here, let me help you with... Don't touch me!

1453
01:19:59,461 --> 01:20:01,910
Everyone clear on the plan? Find Héctor's photo.

1454
01:20:02,005 --> 01:20:03,770
Give it to Miguel. Send Miguel home.

1455
01:20:03,882 --> 01:20:05,009
Got your petals?

1456
01:20:06,719 --> 01:20:08,392
Now, we just have to find de la Cruz.

1457
01:20:08,554 --> 01:20:09,458
Yes?

1458
01:20:10,764 --> 01:20:12,311
Don't I know you?

1459
01:20:13,403 --> 01:20:15,861
That's for murdering the love of my life!

1460
01:20:16,006 --> 01:20:18,131
Who... Who the... She's talking about me!

1461
01:20:18,147 --> 01:20:20,105
I'm the love of your life? I don't know.

1462
01:20:20,107 --> 01:20:21,280
I'm still angry at you.

1463
01:20:21,367 --> 01:20:22,504
Héctor! How did you...

1464
01:20:22,568 --> 01:20:25,516
And that's for trying to murder my grandson.

1465
01:20:25,571 --> 01:20:26,450
Grandson?

1466
01:20:26,452 --> 01:20:27,794
She's talking about me!

1467
01:20:27,796 --> 01:20:28,644
You!

1468
01:20:29,029 --> 01:20:29,834
Wait.

1469
01:20:30,145 --> 01:20:32,032
You're related to Héctor?

1470
01:20:32,036 --> 01:20:33,083
The photo!

1471
01:20:37,583 --> 01:20:38,710
After him!

1472
01:20:40,878 --> 01:20:42,392
Security! Ayúdenme! Security! Help me!

1473
01:20:43,047 --> 01:20:44,589
You said love of your life.

1474
01:20:44,591 --> 01:20:45,972
I don't know what I said.

1475
01:20:46,091 --> 01:20:47,357
That's what I heard.

1476
01:21:01,106 --> 01:21:02,875
Places, Senor. You're on in thirty seconds.

1477
01:21:10,050 --> 01:21:11,963
Ay! Miguel! I have it!

1478
01:21:28,300 --> 01:21:29,597
Hurry! Come on!

1479
01:21:31,519 --> 01:21:33,538
Ladies and gentlemen.

1480
01:21:33,973 --> 01:21:36,143
The one, the only.

1481
01:21:36,271 --> 01:21:39,792
Ernesto de la Cruz!

1482
01:21:48,550 --> 01:21:49,802
Get her off the stage.

1483
01:21:58,330 --> 01:22:00,935
Sing! Sing!

1484
